New Records: Tim Pringle took 3/20, the best bowling figures in the match
Max O'Dowd scored an unbeaten 54, the highest score in the match
Key Match Events: Sompal Kami dropped Vikramjit Singh off Avinash Bohara's bowling
Dipendra Singh Airee dropped a catch of Max O'Dowd off Sompal Kami's bowling
Rohit Kumar Paudel dropped a straightforward catch of Max O'Dowd off Sompal Kami's bowling
Sompal Kami ran out Sybrand Engelbrecht off his own bowling from a fierce strike by Max O'Dowd at the non-striker's end
Post-Match Reflections: Nepal's skipper Rohit Kumar Paudel acknowledged the Dutch bowlers for capitalizing on the early conditions and said they lacked partnerships in the middle, which was the turning point of the game

Dutch skipper Edwards commented, 'The pitch posed challenges, and our bowlers executed their plans well to restrict Nepal. While we would have preferred to achieve the target earlier, the chase became tricky towards the end.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Netherlands secured two points, moving into second position behind South Africa, with both teams having 2 points based on net run rate
Nepal's next match is against Sri Lanka at the Central Broward Park in Florida on June 12th
